overview.eaover:
Each point contains the following information about the parking facility:
Type: Type of lot (public lot, public ramp, private lot, private ramp, on-street,facility)
Name: Name of parking area
Location: Description of location
MonthlyCos: Monthly cost to permit holders
Notes: Additional information
Phone: Organization's phone number
Email: Organization's e-mail contact
Website: Organization's website address
This information was collected from organizations that negotiate pool parking contracts and issue pool parking permits: Metro Transit, St. Paul Smart Trips, Minneapolis Commuter Connection.

descript.abstract: This layer represents locations of all publicly available parking facilities with preferential terms for registered carpools and vanpools.
descript.purpose: To provide location and contact information for preferential pool parking in the Twin Cities.
descript.supplinf: Twin Cities 7 county metropolitan area. This includes the counties of Anoka, Carver, Dakota, Hennepin, Ramsey, Scott and Washington.

procstep.procdesc: The points were located by comparing maps of facilities provided by St. Paul Smart Trips and the Minneapolis Commuter Connection to aerial imagery in ArcGIS
